Polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE) rings are specialized sealing components renowned for their exceptional chemical resistance, high-temperature tolerance, and low friction properties. Typically white in color, PTFE O-rings are favored in applications demanding chemically inert and non-compressible materials. Their unique characteristics make them indispensable in industries where exposure to harsh chemicals, extreme temperatures, and abrasive conditions is common.

Market Size

